1 Section 1. Section 13-2042, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
2 amended to read:
3 13-2042 (1) A disposal fee of two dollars one dollar and thirty-four
4 twenty-five cents is imposed for each six cubic yards of uncompacted
5 solid waste, two dollars one dollar and thirty-four twenty-five cents for
6 each three cubic yards of compacted solid waste, or two dollars one
7 dollar and thirty-four twenty-five cents per ton of solid waste (a)
8 disposed of at landfills regulated by the department or (b) transported
9 for disposal out of state from a solid waste processing facility holding
10 a permit under the Integrated Solid Waste Management Act. Each operator
11 of a landfill or solid waste processing facility shall make the fee
12 payment quarterly. The fee shall be paid quarterly to the department on
13 or before the forty-fifth day following the end of each quarter. For
14 purposes of this section, landfill has the same definition as municipal
15 solid waste landfill unit in 40 C.F.R. 258.2.
16 (2) Each fee payment shall be accompanied by a form prepared and
17 furnished by the department and completed by the permitholder. The form
18 shall state the total volume of solid waste disposed of at the landfill
19 or transported for disposal out of state from the solid waste processing
20 facility during the payment period and shall provide any other
21 information deemed necessary by the department. The form shall be signed
22 by the permitholder.
23 (3) If a permitholder fails to make a timely payment of the fee, he
24 or she shall pay interest on the unpaid amount at the rate specified in
25 section 45-104.02, as such rate may from time to time be adjusted.
26 (4) This section shall not apply to a site used solely for the
27 reclamation of land through the introduction of landscaping rubble or
28 inert material.
29 (5) Sixty-five Fifty percent of the total of such fees collected in
30 each quarter shall be remitted to the State Treasurer for credit to the
31 Integrated Solid Waste Management Cash Fund and shall be used by the
